<h2 class="sectionedit2"><a name="how_do_i_change_my_worm_colour" id="how_do_i_change_my_worm_colour">How do I change my worm colour?</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Depending on the player you are, you use p#_colour to change your worm colour. <a href="doku.php?id=main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:console" class="wikilink1" title="main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:console">open the console</a>, and type:
</p>
<pre class="code">p#_colour &lt;R&gt; &lt;G&gt; &lt;B&gt; (eg . p0_colour 255 0 0, which is red)</pre>

<p>
By default, your player number is 0. However, if you are using splitscreen, the player on the left is p0 and the player on the right is p1. You can also add this into <a href="doku.php?id=main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config" class="wikilink1" title="main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config">config.cfg</a> so that gusanos has this settings every time you run it.
</p>

</div>
